oothing tonic slip down her throat, warming her belly.\r\n\r\n\"Ahh, I\'m not sure.\", she signed, content. \"I may go with the same as my sister. The twin blades.\" She nodded, as if to affirm the thought with herself. Sioranda had chosen the twin blades, in a violent crimson, as a nod both to her role as protector of the faith, and to her family ties. \"In purple, I think. I\'ve always liked purple.\" She let herself smile ever so slightly as her gaze lingered on Gavius.\r\n\r\nHe nodded back with a satisfied \"Hm.\" as she set the cup down and set about vigorously stirring the egg-smothered rice with a pair of chopsticks', 'The Balance of Nature', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '23-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-08-18 16:38:51', '2017-08-18 16:38:51', '', 23, 'http://blog.zenakrua.com/index.php/2017/08/18/23-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
